# .worktreeinclude — gitignored files copied into each new Claude Code worktree.
#
# Uses .gitignore syntax. A file is copied only when it BOTH matches a pattern
# here AND is gitignored AND actually exists — tracked files are never
# duplicated, and missing files are silently skipped (so unused patterns no-op).
# Docs: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees#copy-gitignored-files-into-worktrees
#
# Caspian Security is a self-contained VS Code extension with no backend service
# credentials in the tree. The only gitignored secrets are local env files, so
# those are the only patterns mirrored below: if such a file ever exists locally,
# new worktrees inherit it automatically; until then these lines do nothing.
#
# NOT copied on purpose: node_modules/ (large — run `npm install` per worktree),
# the compiled out/ tree, and packaged *.vsix build artifacts (all regenerated
# by `npm run compile` / `vsce package` inside each worktree).

# Local environment files
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
